title.narrative: Inclusive Dialogue and Enhanced Women's Political Participation

description.narrative:
This project is intended to strengthen the capacity of member countries to address major challenges that impede their ability to conduct more credible and inclusive elections.
In reviewing Commonwealth Observer Group (COG) reports since 1991, the Secretariat has identified two persistent themes in observer recommendations: the importance of inclusive and constructive dialogue between national stakeholders (including election management bodies, political leaders and parties, and civil society) to address tensions and potential triggers for election-related conflict; and the need to address chronically low levels of women’s political participation.
This project will pilot an approach to support member countries in addressing these key challenges through two main components:
Building the capacity of member countries to engage in inclusive and constructive dialogue with national stakeholders, with a view to resolving political impasses, achieving consensus on major issues affecting the credibility of elections, and engaging in conflict prevention throughout the electoral cycle; and
2. Assisting member countries to develop and implement strategies, through consultation with national stakeholders and drawing on good practice, to address the barriers limiting the participation of women in politics.
